May 26-27, 2026: Currency & Cash System Fixes
A systematic currency conversion bug was discovered: all asset prices were stored in their native currency (USD, DKK, GBP) but currentPrice values were being used without GBP conversion. This inflated portfolio values by ~35% (USD prices counted as GBP) and up to 8.6x for DKK assets.
Files fixed across the entire codebase:
- app/api/portfolio/route.ts — Now returns gbpPrice alongside currentPrice for every asset
- app/api/trades/route.ts — Snapshot creation converts prices to GBP before calculating invested value
- app/api/prices/route.ts — Already correct (was converting)
- lib/trading-engine.ts — All signal prices and portfolio values in GBP
- lib/capital-deployment.ts — Deployment prices in GBP
- scripts/update-prices.ts — Snapshot creation uses GBP-converted prices × held quantities
- app/api/bridge/route.ts — Cash balance includes sells
- app/api/cash/route.ts — Cash balance includes sells (2 occurrences)
Sell proceeds bug: When the trading engine executed a sell, it recorded proceeds as a deposit CashTransaction, inflating ISA allowance usage and P&L baseline. Fix: new cash transaction type sell created. Six historical sell transactions reclassified from deposit to sell in the database. All cash balance calculations updated to use (type === "deposit" || type === "sell") ? add : subtract.

 Additional fixes:
- P&L changed from hardcoded totalValue - 1000 to totalValue - sum of actual deposits across all snapshot creation points
- Snapshot invested value changed from summing one unit per asset to heldQuantity × gbpPrice for each holding
- Cash balance now correctly includes sell transactions in all 7 files that calculate it
- Zero TypeScript compilation errors across entire codebase
